<h1 class="hero-h">Claude Projects vs Custom GPTs: <em>head-to-head.</em></h1>
<p class="hero-sub">Claude Projects and Custom GPTs both let you package context + instructions + reusable workflows into shareable artifacts. They look similar. They're actually different in ways that matter for what you can build.</p>
<div class="verdict"><div class="verdict-l">The take</div><p class="verdict-p">These get positioned as competing but they solve different problems. <strong>Claude Projects</strong> is designed for internal team use: you load 20-30 documents (style guide, past strategy, ICP research), everyone on Claude Team gets the same context, and Claude answers using it. There's no store, no discovery, no public URL. That's the point. It's a private team workspace. <strong>Custom GPTs</strong> solve for public-facing agents: anyone on ChatGPT can find yours, use it, or subscribe. For internal work with heavy document context, Claude Projects wins. For customer-facing agents you want discoverable, Custom GPTs still wins.</p></div>
</div></div>

<div style="background:#0A1A0A;border-top:1px solid #1A3A1A;border-bottom:1px solid #1A3A1A;padding:1.25rem 2.5rem;">
<div style="max-width:880px;margin:0 auto;display:flex;justify-content:space-between;align-items:center;gap:1rem;flex-wrap:wrap;font-size:0.78rem;color:#8FAF8F;">
<div>By <a href="/about" style="color:#F0FFF0;text-decoration:none;font-weight:500;">Bill Colbert</a> · <span style="color:#4A6A4A;">Founder, Treetop Growth Strategy</span></div>
<div style="color:#4A6A4A;">Published May 2026 · <a href="/content-library" style="color:#8FAF8F;text-decoration:none;">More from the library</a></div>
</div>
</div>

<section><div class="sec-inner"><h2 class="h2">What Claude Projects actually are</h2><p class="body">A Claude Project is a persistent workspace with: custom instructions (your system prompt), context files (PDFs, docs, brand guides), and conversation history. Available on Claude Team and Enterprise plans. Best fit: workflows that benefit from large context (research, document analysis, long-running projects) and from Claude's reasoning depth.</p></div></section>
<section><div class="sec-inner"><h2 class="h2">What Custom GPTs actually are</h2><p class="body">A Custom GPT is a packaged ChatGPT configuration with: instructions, knowledge files, and (optionally) actions (API calls to external tools). Available on ChatGPT Plus, Team, Enterprise. Best fit: team-distributable utility prompts ('our brand voice GPT', 'our pricing Q&A GPT') and creative work where DALL-E or vision matter.</p></div></section>
<section><div class="sec-inner"><h2 class="h2">Where Claude Projects win</h2><p class="body">Five real advantages:<br><br>1. <strong>Reasoning quality.</strong> Claude is consistently stronger on complex multi-step reasoning, nuanced writing, and instruction following.<br>2. <strong>Context handling.</strong> Claude handles large context windows more gracefully, useful for document analysis, research synthesis.<br>3. <strong>Long-form output.</strong> Claude produces more usable long-form content with less editing.<br>4. <strong>Brand voice consistency.</strong> Projects maintain voice better than Custom GPTs over many uses.<br>5. <strong>Sensitive data handling.</strong> Anthropic's data policies are friendlier for client/proprietary work.</p></div></section>
<section><div class="sec-inner"><h2 class="h2">Where Custom GPTs win</h2><p class="body">Five real advantages:<br><br>1. <strong>Ecosystem.</strong> The GPT Store has thousands of pre-built options. Many are useful.<br>2. <strong>Multimodal.</strong> Built-in DALL-E for images. Voice mode. Vision capabilities deeper than Claude's.<br>3. <strong>Custom Actions.</strong> Can call your APIs directly without separate orchestration.<br>4. <strong>Team distribution.</strong> Slightly easier to share with non-technical teammates.<br>5. <strong>Cost at scale.</strong> If you're already paying for ChatGPT Team for the team, Custom GPTs come included.</p></div></section>
<section><div class="sec-inner"><h2 class="h2">Which to use for which job</h2><p class="body"><strong>Use Claude Projects for:</strong> long-form writing, document analysis, research synthesis, complex reasoning, anything brand-sensitive, multi-document workflows, proprietary client work.<br><br><strong>Use Custom GPTs for:</strong> quick utility prompts shared across team, image generation workflows, voice-driven workflows, custom API actions, anything multimodal.</p></div></section>
<section><div class="sec-inner"><h2 class="h2">How most B2B teams should set up</h2><p class="body">The pattern that works for most B2B mid-market teams in 2026:<br><br>1. <strong>Default to Claude Team ($30/seat)</strong> with 5-10 core Projects for the highest-value workflows (Strategy, Content, Reporting, ICP, Customer Voice).<br>2. <strong>Add ChatGPT Team ($30/seat)</strong> if you need multimodal/voice/Custom GPT ecosystem.<br>3. <strong>Train the team</strong> on which to use for which job. The rule of thumb: long writing or complex reasoning → Claude. Quick utility or multimodal → ChatGPT.<br><br>Total cost: $60/seat/month. Trade-off: two tools, two interfaces, two prompt patterns. Worth it for most teams.</p></div></section>
<section><div class="sec-inner"><h2 class="h2">When to run only one</h2><p class="body">Run Claude only if: you're cost-constrained, your work is overwhelmingly text-based, your team is small enough that two tools is overhead.<br><br>Run ChatGPT only if: you're heavy on multimodal work, your team is already deep in the OpenAI ecosystem, you need broader integration via Custom Actions.<br><br>For most B2B work in 2026, running both is the right answer.</p></div></section>

<section><div class="sec-inner"><h2 class="h2">Comparison</h2><table class="compare-table"><thead><tr><th>Dimension</th><th>Claude Projects</th><th>Custom GPTs</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td>Reasoning quality</td><td>Stronger</td><td>Good</td></tr>
<tr><td>Long-form writing</td><td>Stronger</td><td>Good (more editing)</td></tr>
<tr><td>Brand voice consistency</td><td>Better</td><td>Drifts more</td></tr>
<tr><td>Multimodal (image/voice)</td><td>Limited</td><td>Native (DALL-E, voice)</td></tr>
<tr><td>Custom API actions</td><td>Via separate orchestration</td><td>Built-in</td></tr>
<tr><td>Ecosystem/marketplace</td><td>Smaller</td><td>GPT Store (thousands)</td></tr>
<tr><td>Pricing</td><td>$30/seat Team</td><td>$30/seat Team</td></tr>
<tr><td>Best for</td><td>Knowledge work, brand-sensitive</td><td>Team utility, multimodal</td></tr></tbody></table></div></section>

